    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Film genre considered to be a sub-genre of horror or fantasy films, in the way that deal both deal with improbable creatures and improbable worlds. Science fiction films tend to use science fiction literature as their source material or it projects the possible development of a speculative future, such as the overpopulated and violent ones found such films as "Soylent Green" (1973) and "Blade Runner (1982), Science fiction and horror can certainly created hybrid films such as "The Terminator" (1984).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047993/Konigsberg, The Complete Film Dictionary (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Filmgenre dat wordt beschouwd als een subgenre van horror- of fantasyfilms, omdat ook deze films gaan over onwaarschijnlijke wezens in onwaarschijnlijke werelden. Sciencefictionfilms gebruiken vaak sciencefictionliteratuur als bronmateriaal of schetsen de mogelijke ontwikkeling van een speculatieve toekomst, waarin bijvoorbeeld overbevolking en geweld een belangrijke rol spelen. Voorbeelden hiervan zijn de films 'Soylent Green' (1973) en 'Blade Runner' (1982). Sciencefiction en horror kunnen ook worden gecombineerd tot hybride films, zoals 'The Terminator' (1984).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>此種電影類型被視為有關超現實生物和世界的恐怖片或奇幻電影的次類型。科幻電影通常運用科幻文學作為創作素材，或是可以預測未來的可能發展，例如在西元1973年的《超世紀諜殺案》（Soylent Green）和西元1982年的《銀翼殺手》（Blade Runner）即出現人口過剩及充滿暴力的未來世界。科幻電影和恐怖片也能結合製作出混合電影，如西元1984年的《魔鬼終結者》（The Terminator）。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gênero cinematográfico considerado um subgênero dos filmes de terror ou fantasia, na medida em que tratam tanto de criaturas improváveis quanto de mundos improváveis. Os filmes de ficção científica tendem a usar a literatura de ficção científica como fonte de material ou projetam o possível desenvolvimento de um futuro especulativo, como os superpovoados e violentos encontrados em filmes como "Soylent Green" (1973) e "Blade Runner (1982), Ficção científica e terror certamente podem criar filmes híbridos como "O Exterminador do Futuro" (1984).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
